# 1.Write a Python program that asks the user for their name and age, then prints a personalized greeting message. Use both the + operator and f-strings for output?
# Taking input from user
name = input("Enter your name: ")
age = input("Enter your age: ")
# Using + operator
print("Hello " + name + "! You are " + age + " years old.")
# Using f-strings
print(f"Nice to meet you, {name}! Next year, you will be {int(age) + 1} years old.")


# 2.String Manipulation Exercise: Write a Python program that Takes a sentence as input from the user.Prints the sentence in all uppercase and lowercase.Replaces all spaces with underscores.
Removes leading and trailing whitespace.
Sentence = input("Enter sentence: ")
print("Uppercase: ",Sentence.upper())
print("Lowercase: ",Sentence.lower())
print(Sentence.replace(" ","_"))
print(Sentence.strip())


